	<h1>Taiwan Stock Market Individual Broker</h1>
	<table border="0">
	<tbody>
	<tr>
		<br>
       <p>
       &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; For individual broker, we implement the feature of showing the edges (associations) when they are linked to one individual node (broker) when right clicking on it. 
       That is, the visualization shows edges from/to one particular broker.</p>
		<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; In Figure 1, we shows edges from/to one individual broker in three levels (0.1, 0.01, 0.001) with discrete Blue, Green, and Red colors. 
		Furthermore, we adopt the absolute values of 2 based logarithm P-values (|log2(P-value)|) in Figure 2 for better (less tilted) distribution with gradient milder Blue to Red color, 
		Since the majority of P-values are close to 0 and the amount of P-values also increase gradually to the direction of 0 (see the distribution of true P-value in <a href="distribution.html">Value Distribution</a> page).</p>
     <br>
